dering the accuracies when applied to the DL-based\nhigh-resolution multiclass classifier (HMC) of CAs. In our experiments, we\ndownsampled the ECG signals from the CPSC2018 dataset and evaluated their HMC\naccuracies with and without the SRECG. Experimental results show that SRECG can\nwell improve the HMC accuracies as compared to traditional interpolation\nmethods. Moreover, approximately half of the CAs classification accuracies of\nHMC were maintained within the enhanced ECG signals by SRECG. The promising\nresults confirm that SRECG can be suitably used to enhance low-resolution ECG\nsignals from P/W devices with CE to improve their cloud-based HMC performances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Dec 2020 15:43:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 15 Jan 2023 09:53:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
